Docker ke 3 main components:

| Component           | Kaam                                                                               |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Docker Client**   | CLI se commands dete ho — `docker build`, `docker run`                             |
| **Docker Daemon**   | Background mein kaam karta hai — images build karna, containers chalana            |
| **Docker Registry** | Images store karta hai — Docker Hub (public) ya Azure Container Registry (private) |


Docker Image vs Container :- 
1. Image = Blueprint/template (read-only) — jaise class in programming
2. Container = Running instance of image — jaise object


Commands Piyush dikhata hai:


docker build -t myapp .      # Image banana
docker run -p 3000:3000 myapp  # Container chalana
docker ps                     # Running containers dekho
docker stop <container-id>    # Container band karo